The streets of Port Elizabeth (PE) are abuzz as Springbok fans are waiting for the bus with the champions and the Webb Ellis cup to pass them. From early Sunday morning fans were outside the hotel were the players are staying, hoping to see their favourite players. The tour has started at the City Hall. Despite the cold and wet weather conditions, Springbok fans have come out in numbers to see the champions carrying the Webb Ellis Cup through Nelson Mandela Bay. This is the home of Captain Siya Kolisi, Coach Rassie Erasmus and backline coach Mzwandile Stick. The Springbok tour will include areas such as Zwide, KwaZakhele and Uitenhage. Excited fans throughout the metro are waiting in anticipation for the champions. Watch video below for more on the story:  